headline: Coca-Cola Extends Dividend Streak As New Leadership Shapes Cash Priorities
summary: Coca-Cola (NYSE:KO) announced its 64th consecutive annual dividend increase, extending a multi decade record of shareholder payouts. The company also named Todd Beiger as vice president and head of investor relations and confirmed a CEO transition from James Quincey to Henrique Braun. These moves come as Coca-Cola continues to adjust its product lineup and packaging, including a focus on smaller and more affordable formats.
